codex
`Dashboard` now renders the SSH vault on the Home screen and wires its actions into the existing dashboard state. The new panel is mounted in [Dashboard.tsx](/home/hun/Volume/DEVLEOPMENT/Orbit/.orchestrator/sessions/20260322_143717_-translate_SSH_연결_저장_및_재사용_기능_추가/agents/agent-03/worktree/src/components/dashboard/Dashboard.tsx#L1328), the SSH form can open in `project` or `vault` mode via the added state and callbacks in [Dashboard.tsx](/home/hun/Volume/DEVLEOPMENT/Orbit/.orchestrator/sessions/20260322_143717_-translate_SSH_연결_저장_및_재사용_기능_추가/agents/agent-03/worktree/src/components/dashboard/Dashboard.tsx#L112) and [Dashboard.tsx](/home/hun/Volume/DEVLEOPMENT/Orbit/.orchestrator/sessions/20260322_143717_-translate_SSH_연결_저장_및_재사용_기능_추가/agents/agent-03/worktree/src/components/dashboard/Dashboard.tsx#L598). I also relaxed the right-pane render condition so an inline session can still show even without the normal project-selected Home branch in [Dashboard.tsx](/home/hun/Volume/DEVLEOPMENT/Orbit/.orchestrator/sessions/20260322_143717_-translate_SSH_연결_저장_및_재사용_기능_추가/agents/agent-03/worktree/src/components/dashboard/Dashboard.tsx#L1264).

Because this branch did not contain `SshVaultPanel`, I added a minimal implementation in [SshVaultPanel.tsx](/home/hun/Volume/DEVLEOPMENT/Orbit/.orchestrator/sessions/20260322_143717_-translate_SSH_연결_저장_및_재사용_기능_추가/agents/agent-03/worktree/src/components/dashboard/SshVaultPanel.tsx#L1). Its Quick Connect path currently creates an SSH/DOCKER project from the saved profile and then creates a terminal session, which is what the dashboard opens inline. That is the smallest working path with the current API surface, since there is no adhoc SSH-session endpoint in this codebase.

Verified with `npx tsc --noEmit` and updated [tasks/todo.md](/home/hun/Volume/DEVLEOPMENT/Orbit/.orchestrator/sessions/20260322_143717_-translate_SSH_연결_저장_및_재사용_기능_추가/agents/agent-03/worktree/tasks/todo.md#L4).
